ce:section.ce:para:
Raman spectra of the solvents and [Li(EC or FEC)
                           x
                        ][FSA] (x = 1.5, 2, 3, 4, 8, 10, 20, 30 and 50) were obtained using a laser Raman spectrometer (NRS-4100, JASCO equipped with 27 mW and 785 nm laser) at a resolution of ~4 cm−1 and calibrated using a polypropylene standard. The temperature of the samples was adjusted to 30 °C, except for EC, [Li(EC)30][FSA], and [Li(EC)50][FSA] (40 °C), during the measurement using a Peltier microscope stage (TS62, INSTEC) with a temperature controller (mk1000, INSTEC). To analyze the coordination of Li+–EC/FEC and Li+–[FSA]−, the Raman signal intensities were normalized via the signals of each solvent at 1483 cm−1 for EC and 1465 cm−1 for FEC. These normalized signals were additionally weighted by the molarities of each solvent.
